{"questionId":"18880","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Aspirin is formed by reacting salicylic acid with ethanoic anhydride. The structure of aspirin is given in section 37 of the data booklet.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/6607021398d14bff0315d2a597cad7ef5ec76b82.png\" width=\"404\" height=\"144\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The solubility of aspirin is increased by converting it to an ionic form. Draw the structure of the ionic form of aspirin.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/996cf198330296f0abcff864339a9feb53a9d389.png\">✔</p>\n<p><br><em>Accept a positive metal ion next to the <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mi>O</mi><msup><mi>O</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">-</mo></msup></math>&nbsp;such as “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mi>N</mi><msup><mi>a</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">+</mo></msup><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">/</mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">+</mo></msup></math>”.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>−</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>N</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>/</mo><mo>−</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>K</mi></math>” without showing the charges.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept notations such as “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mi>C</mi><mi>O</mi><msup><mi>O</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></math>” <strong>OR</strong> “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mi>C</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>N</mi><mi>a</mi></math>” <strong>OR</strong> “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mi>C</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>K</mi></math>” but not “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><msup><mi>O</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></math>” <strong>OR</strong> “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>N</mi><mi>a</mi></math>” <strong>OR</strong> “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>K</mi></math>”.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"18880","referenceCode":"20N.3.sl.TZ0.11c","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The solubility of aspirin is increased by converting it to an ionic form. Draw the structure of the ionic form of aspirin.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.2 Aspirin and penicillin","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}